r:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FG022526%2F1"><gtr:id>76915706-A34C-4AED-BBE6-068469D78F6E</gtr:id><gtr:title>Poverty, Poor Relief and Economic Development in Engand. c. 1590-1720</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/G022526/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>England was the first country in Europe to instigate a nationwide system of relief for the poor. Although much has been written about the English Poor Laws, the character of the poverty they relieved is inadequately understood. In particular, historians have relied on records of individual doles, often linked to records of vital events, in order to study the kinds of hardship that led people to require poor relief. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The doctoral research on which the fellowship will be based used hitherto underexploited sources, namely many hundreds of petitions by individual paupers for relief, to provide an extremely detailed study (based on the county of Lancashire) of the forms and causes of poverty in early modern England. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The year will be spent publishing major research from the thesis, on the development of formal poor relief provision in early modern England, the character of poverty as relieved by this formal provision, and the timing and nature of economic crises&amp;nbsp;- and especially their impact on the poor - in the late seventeenth century. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>Finally, research, compiled during the course of the doctorate, on the gendered impact of famine in early modern England will be published.&lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2009-09-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2009-04-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>30859</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>08838D08-A1D1-475F-8CEC-0D98053297CD</gtr:id><gtr:title>Poverty in an industrializing town: deserving hardship in Bolton, 1674&amp;acirc;??99</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Social History</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/92276d33e016dc76ce5166c1e8ab2437"><gtr:id>92276d33e016dc76ce5166c1e8ab2437</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Healey J</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>56dedc9c476aa5.45356597</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>AEC65E11-2149-4950-99D9-F99684752E34</gtr:id><gtr:title>The First Century of Welfare: Poverty and Poor Relief in Lancashire, 1620-1730</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/3e49340b116066bfa778921354d88b39"><gtr:id>3e49340b116066bfa778921354d88b39</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Healey Jonathan</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>9781843839569</gtr:isbn><gtr: